{"author":{"id":"30a9cdd9e5369167dc36be4d3e5f98e516aa30b7571a17013bc815eef45f09c3"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1445375364,"nonce":"oQj77jJ1bSPA5QNUMKciVVfpihY=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE0OTcwNDIxNg==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/345#issuecomment-149704216"},"message":"@natefoo okay, I'll add this as a feature. You'll be able to request two types of proxied packages:\n- served from a local copy\n- redirects to existing URLs\n\nBut I worry that we don't really gain so much with that, and that we're just trading one backend that could disappear for another backend.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1445399102,"nonce":"D1+T6ZMln7CMEtwHMaBTpaJlxA4=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE0OTc3MjM3Mw==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/345#issuecomment-149772373"},"message":"@bgruening @peterjc @natefoo @martenson \n\nOkay... it's done! In the form of a 42 line python file and a urls.tsv file. \n- in lieu of \"accounts\" and \"approval\" process, we use a github repository and PRs.\n- in lieu of an actual proxy, the script just downloads the URLs to files named after their sha256sum, and lets nginx/etc serve them up.\n- in lieu of databases or any of that nonsense, there's a dead simple tab separated file which consists of three columns: (sha256, url, optional comment).\n- in lieu of nate's request for redirects ... hmm. I didn't solve that one. (Sorry Nate!)\n- in lieu of requests like `https://package-server/?url=https://...` we'll make requests like `https://package-server/path/to/dir/shaaaa256suuuuum#https://the-real-url`, appending the real url as a URL fragment to the end (ignored on serving files) in order to preserve some end-user transparency of which files are being downloaded.\n\nI'd like to:\n- [ ] set up a repository for this (galaxyproject or galaxy-iuc?)\n- [ ] set up a jenkins job to run the downloader\n- [ ] get the directory this script outputs to served by some webserver.\n\n\u003cs\u003eI'll begin pre-seeding\u003c/s\u003e finished pre-seeding the file with all of the IUC's URLs/sha256sums.","files":null}]}